##Number 4: Wisconsin Tornadoes Web Map

import geopandas as gpd
import pandas as pd
import folium

#read files
tornadoes = gpd.read_file('/data/classes/2025/spring/geog435/clemenjd0687/lab_08/torn.geojson')  # or .shp
wisconsin_counties = gpd.read_file('/data/classes/2025/spring/geog435/clemenjd0687/lab_08/wi_counties.geojson')

#projecting data to epsg 3070
tornadoes_3070 = tornadoes.to_crs(epsg=3070)
wisconsin_3070 = wisconsin_counties.to_crs(epsg=3070)

#WI Tornadoe clip
tornadoes_clipped = gpd.clip(tornadoes_3070, wisconsin_3070)

tornadoes_final = tornadoes_clipped.to_crs(epsg=4326)
In [16]:
#Map
# Center on Wisconsin
map_center = [44.5, -89.5]  # general center of Wisconsin
m = folium.Map(location=map_center, zoom_start=6)

# Add tornado points with conditional coloring
for _, row in tornadoes_final.iterrows():
    lat = row.geometry.y
    lon = row.geometry.x
    fatal = row['FATAL'] if 'FATAL' in row else 0  # Adjust column name if needed
    color = 'red' if fatal > 0 else 'blue'
    
    folium.Marker(
        location=[lat, lon],
        icon=folium.Icon(color=color),
    ).add_to(m)

# Add layer control and display map
folium.LayerControl().add_to(m)
display(m)
